      • writeRest

        void writeRest(byte[] blob,
             int count)
               throws IOException
        Writes byte blob of unknown data from next versions of model. If used, this method should be called after all the known fields of user type are written.
        Parameters:
        blob - the data to write
        count - the actual length of data in supplied blob
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O error occurred.
